"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-when-are-team-sa-in-paris-olympics-action-wednesday-31-july\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbWhen are Team SA in Olympics action on Wednesday?  A host of Team SA athletes will be in action at the Olympics on Wednesday. Here are all the times to take note of so you do not miss a thing.  On Wednesday, there will once again be plenty of attention on the exploits of Team SA's first gold medallist, Tatjana Smith, who returns to the pool.  The swimming superstarwill be hoping to take a few laps towards another gold medalas she takes part in the heats and - almost certainly - the200m breaststrokesemi-finals.  Team SA start Wednesday with three Olympics medals, with the men's sevens rugby bronze medal and Alan Hatherly (bronze) added to Smith's gold lifting them to 12th place on the overall table  ARCHERY  Men's individual 1/32 limination round (7.16pm):Wiaan Roux vs Je Deok Kim (Kor)  HOCKEY  Women's Pool B (10.30am):Team SA vs Great Britain  Men's Pool A (7.45pm):Team SA vs Spain  ROWING  Women's singles scull, semi-finals C/D (10.24am):Paige Badenhorst. Note: Badenhorst is competing for 13th to 24th position  Men's pair, semi-final A/B (10.34am):John Smith and Christoher Baxter. How it works: There are two semi-finals of six boats. The first three in each go into final A and the remainder into final B. The medals come from final A  SWIMMING  Women's 200m breaststroke heats (11am):Tatjana Smith, Kaylene Corbett  Men's 200m backstroke, heats (11.27am):Pieter Coetze  Men's 200m backstroke, semi-finals (9.47pm):Pieter Coetze  Women's 200m breaststroke semi-finals (10.03pm):Tatjana Smith, Kaylene Corbett  TRIATHLON  Women's individual (8am):Vicky van der Merwe  Men's individual (10.45am):Henri Schoeman and James Riddle  Compiled byTeam SA websitein Paris  TUESDAY, 30 JULY  CYCLING (BMX)  Men's park qualificationVincent Leygonie was unable to finish in the top 9 and was eliminated after placing 12th with a points average of 75.85 after two runs  HOCKEY  Men's Pool A:Team SA 1 Germany 5  ROWING  Women's single sculls, quarter-finals:Paige Bandenhorst finished fourth in her quarter-final. How it works: The first three from each of the four heats progress to semi-finals A/B. The remainder go through to semi-finals C/D. Badenhorst therefore will be competing for places 13th to 24th.  RUGBY SEVENS  Women's 11th/12th pace playoff: Team SA 21 Fiji 15  SURFING  Women's third round: POSTPONEDSarah Baum vs Clarissa Moore  SWIMMING  Men's 200m butterfly, heats:Matthew Sates finished 6th in 1:57.04. That p[aced him 20th on the overall time sheets and he missed out on a place in the semi-finals.  TRIATHLON  Men's Individual: POSTPONEDJamie Riddle and Henri Schoeman. The event will now be held on Wednesday    WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"